        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> rvolosatovs submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13620#pullrequestreview-4484629161\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 602466383,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781259254
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> rvolosatovs created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13620#discussion_r3402492859\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm not sure if this should be gated by <code>custom</code> feature, but the comment in <code>stackswitch</code> states:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>   // No support for this platform. Don&#39;t fail compilation though and\n   // instead defer the error to happen at runtime when a fiber is created.\n   // Should help keep compiles working and narrows the failure to only\n   // situations that need fibers on unsupported platforms.\n</code></pre></div>\n\n</blockquote>\n<p>so this seems consistent</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 602466386,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781259254
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>github-actions[bot] added the label <code>wasmtime:api</code> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13620\">PR #13620</a>.</p>",
        "id": 602527204,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781272018
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13620#pullrequestreview-4486878617\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Sounds reasonable to me, thanks!</p>\n<p>Structurally though I'd like to plumb this a bit differently to ensure this shows up in the <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/main/examples/min-platform/embedding/wasmtime-platform.h\"><code>wasmtime-platform.h</code> header file</a>. That header is generated from <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/main/crates/wasmtime/src/runtime/vm/sys/custom/capi.rs\">this file</a> and is the current source-of-truth for \"wasmtime may externally rely on these things\" and provides a nice place to document things as well.</p>\n<p>Now if these C API definitions were added over there they wouldn't actually be usable in <code>wasmtime-internal-fiber</code> due to crate dependencies, but that's also fine to have them duplicated here. Basically, can you add these function definitions over there, document them as to their purpose, leave a provisional comment in both locations saying \"hey this is duplicated over there keep them in-sync\", and then regenerate the header file?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 602558405,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781277441
    },
